Well, this is what you want to know, Mrs Frances, the story of Jos Santos Noco Guaji.
bueno eto pwooo to pechoyore veno Pransiska , eto mayee historia ema Jos Santos Noko Guaji .
Bueno eso quiere saber seora Francisca la historia de Jos Santos Noco Guaji.
When he was a soldier, the man was a comrade of my grand-father, the father of my father.
ema te to sontaapo , ema chane makochane ema ma nochko nuti , mueya ma tata ,
l cuando fu soldado, el hombre fu compnero de mi abuelo, el padre de mi pap,
People, when they white people arrived, people did not want... people did not want the white people to enter, they wanted to kill them, because this was the order of Pedro Ignacio Muiva.
eno chaono te to titekpompo eno tkomeriono , eno wo nawrorii eno no chaono ... wo nawrorii to tsiopano eno tkomeriono , nawooo to nakopaka eno , jicho eto mawoniipiii ma Pedro Ignacio Muiva .

la gente cuando llegaron los carayanas (gente blanca), ellos no queran a esa gente... no queran que entren los carayanas (gente blanca), lo queran matar a ellos, porque eso era mandato de Pedro Ignacio Muiba.
And so the white people did not want to... they did not leave the white people enter.
ene takeei eno no chaono tkomeriono wo nawroo to ... wo naesopa no chane tkomeriono to tsiopano .
traduction sens inverse de la phrase prcdente ???
Es as que la gente carayana no queran el...no la dejaron los carayanas a la gente entrar.
And people went there, here they killed people, they whipped them.
ene tyonompo eno chaono onogi , te pjoka nakoparakpo eno no chaono , naestarakopo .
Y se fueron la gente all, aqu los mataron a la gente, los guasquearon.
Pedro Ignacio Muiva said: "Do not run off, I... um... we are going to kill them" he said.
ema Pedro Ignacio Muiva makepo ema : " wo akujnopo nuti manjeeyore pnoono vkopakoyre " makepo .
Pedro Ignacio Muiba dijo: "No escapen, yo les voy a hacer... estos vamos a matar" dijo.
edro Ignacio Muiba dijo no escapen yo les voy a hacer ver a estos, los vamos a matar dijo.

And he ordered this to the people who were his soldiers. And they escaped, when he got hit, they hit Pedro Ignacio, they killed him, they attached him (like oxen), they hit him, they cut him. He was still defending himself, but his fellows had run away. That's how they won over him.

ene eno no chaono sontaronrii mayee ema , ene mawonikpo , asike tjunopookompo eno ( to ) te tkenapo , naeopo ma Pedro Ignacio , nakopakopo namuujokpo , naeopo , naechkopo ; ema tkotyuchworichini , pero no majanemuriono tjunopookompo : takeei naetoakpo ema .
tke'napo cette analyse ne va pas. tkejnapo ???

Y la gente que eran sus soldados de l los mand, as es que escaparon ellos, cuando fu pegado (golpeado), le pegaron a Pedro Ignacio, lo mataron, lo abueycaron (lo ataron entre muchos), lo pegaron, lo cortaron, l an se defenda; pero sus compaeros estaban escapando, as es que lo vencieron a l.
ene nakuchokupo eno chaono onogi te to nowrikrii no pomriono , tyuumutompo , nakuchokupo te to nakopayakaripka to komisin , ma taetpikpo ema Jos Santos Noko Guaji sontaarii ema nawonikpo , tyonompo .

Y la gente los esper (emboscada) all, donde estaban, donde estaban los otros, se reunieron, los esperaron si es que los alcanzaba la comison, le toc estar a Jos Santos Noco Guaji como soldado, a l lo mandaron, se fu.
There, the soldiers, the soldiers were ten, they were going to reach at... the people.
onogi , sontarono , diesnano no sontarono tyononrii nakopayako te (@) no chane ,
All, soldados, eran diez los soldados se fueron a alcanzar ??? de la gente
And there, the people were strengthening in the woods.
ene onogi no chaono teyjuchwompo te to smeno .
y all la gente se defendieron en el monte.
And when the ones on the committee arrived and entered on their horses, the people caught them.
ene to titekpompo eno tsiopono tkoperojono eno no komisiononrii , nakopayako no chaono .
Y cuando llegaron entraron montados los que iban comisionados, los alcanzaron a la gente.
And them, they used a lasso, they tied it to a tree.
ene eno , nanokpuiji to laso , [ nae ] naemitjiko to ... te to ykugi .
Y ellos, se dice que pusieron el lazo, lo amarraron al...en el rbol.
So that when all the ones on horses entered, they started to shoot arrows, they killed them.
asike te tsiopompo namutu eno tkoperojonrii , nanaekchopo nakoyusrepo , nakoparakpo .
As es que cuando entraron todos los que venan montados comenzaron a flecharlos, los mataron.

And one of the man was good and knew how to ride, because when he arrived, when they were going to come out where there was a rope, then um... they stretched out the rope, the horse arrived and when it arrived there, it couldn't pass the rope.

ene ema ma tona , tyuuna muetkopka to tkpero ema chane , porke te to titekpo , tyuchkonyorepuiji te to towo to wkapi , ene [ naa ] manjee nakojarupkopo to wkapi , titekpopo to kwoyu enepo taechiso wipo taatoo [ taet ] tanukaai to wkapi .

Y uno de ellos bueno, que seguramente saba montar el hombre, porque cuando lleg, cuando ya iba a salir donde estaba la guasca e este la extendieron la guasca lleg el caballo all lleg ya no pudo trancarlo la guasca.
And one of them knew how to ride, sent by God, they shouldn't kill him.
ene ema ma tona muetko tkopero mawoniru ma viya , ema wo nakpakyore ema chane
Y uno de ellos saba montar, enviado por Dios, l, ese hombre no debian matarlo,
The horse saw when they stretch out the rope, the horse jumped and passed the rope, so that he ran and went.
taemopo to kwoyu to [ na ] nakojarupkopo to wkapi , teterekpo eto kwoyu tanukpo to wkapi , asike ema tjunopopo tyompo .
el caballo vi cuando la extendieron la guasca, salt el caballo logr cruzar la guasca, as es que el corri y se fu.
When he went, the others chased him, he was far away already, God had pity on him, they did not catch up with him.
to tyompo ema , naponojokpo no pomriono , ema ewireripo , majapanu ma Viya , wo nakopayaka .
Cuando el se fu, lo persiguieron los otros, l ya estaba lejos, le tuvo lstima Dios, no lo alcanzarn.
It is him who informed the people when he arrived here in town.
emapo mametokopo eno chaono , te pjoka titekpopo te to wsare ,
Fu el quien le avis a la gente aqu cuando lleg al pueblo,
He informed the commandant, the one of the committee informed the soldiers too, that they had been chasing him, that they killed the others.
mametokopo ema te to ... ma comandante , nae no militariono , enopo mametokooi ema ma komisionrii to naponojokrii , nakoparako no pomriono .
le avis al comandante, a los militares tambin los avis l que era comisionado, que los corretearon, que los mataron a los otros.
Well, "well, we are going to send a hundred soldiers" he said. They sent another committee, they went, they went to the place where the others had been killed.
Bueno , " tyuri viopjukyore sien soldado " makoe , nopjukpo pona komisin , tyonompo , tyonompo te to nakoparaso no pomriono .
Bueno, "bueno vamos a enviar cien soldados" dijo, enviaron otra comisin, se fueron, se fueron hacia donde los mataron a los otros.
It was his turn as a soldier, Santos Noco Guaji, he was accompanied by my grand-father, they went, he was with a hundred, a hundred people.
taetpikpo ema Jose Santos Noko Waji sontaarii ema makochane ema nochko , tyonompo , makochaneei eno no sien , siengiene sontaru .
Le toc estar como soldado a Jos Santos Noco Guaji, l estaba con mi abuelo, se fueron, l acompao a los cien, los cien soldados.
When they arrived there, they (the others) left them enter, they entered and they were ready with their arrows to kill the soldiers, the soldiers were carrying shotguns, guns, whatever.
Te titekpompo oni , naesopo to tsioponrii eno , nakosioproko ene ttsetsekwonripo to tagiigire to [ nakopa ] nakopasiyore no sontarono , eno sontarono eno tyomonrii to eskopeta , fusi , tajpuka eto .
nogi, tsetsekwonripo. Florencia 2018 confirme que nakosioproko

Cuando llegaron all, los dejaron que hayan entrado, ellos los dejaron en ingresar y estaban preparados con las flechas listas para matarlos a los soldados, los soldados llevaban escopeta, fusil, de todo.
And the trinitarios were warrying only arrows, so that they were scared.
Ene eno trinranono tagiigirechus to nomrii asike tpikompo ,
Y los trinitarios solamente llevaban flechas as es que tuvieron miedo,
And it was the turn of the soldiers to enter, they shot arrows at them.
y ellos (soldados) precisamente ingresaron, los flechearon
And they were going to shoot arrows at Santos Noco, he spoke in our language: "Don't kill me, me too I am your relative."
ene ema nayukyorepuini ema Jos Santos Noko , techjikpo te to vechjiriiwo : " wo akukpaknu nutirichu ajaonnu .
y a Jos Santos Noco ya lo iban a flechear y l habl en nuestro idioma : no me maten yo tambin soy pariente de ustedes.
es que eno , nuti sontaanuui twoniknonrii pero nuti wo , wo naksiojwoyre wo [ nakpara ] wo nakpakeyre eti njaonono .
es que ellos, yo soy soldado me han mandado, pero yo no, no me meter no [ ] no los voy a matar a ustedes mis parientes.
-Good, leave your shirt", theytold him, because he was a soldier, they gave him a civil shirt.
tyuri pnokjigia pjo pkmisa " najichpo ema , jicho sontaarii ema , naejrokpo to camisa civil .
- Bueno dejala tu camisa" le dijeron a l, porque l era soldado, le dieron camisa civil.
So my grand-father was with him, they were two the ones who were speaking our language, that's why they have not killed them.
Asike emapo ma nochko ema makochaneei , apinano eno techjikonrii te to vechjiriiwo , takeei to wipo nakopakaai .
As que mi abuelo lo estaba acompaando, eran dos ellos que hablaban en nuestro idioma, por eso es que ya no los mataron.
And they went out, um... they went with the killers, the trinitarios, the others were chasing the other people.
Ene tyuchkuompo eno , [ na ] manjee , nakochanepo eno no tkopaiono , no trinranono , eno no pomriono naponojokpo no pomri chaono .
Y salieron ellos, [ ] este, los acompaaron a los matones, los trinitarios, los otros los corretearon a la otra gente.
They went in there, the place called San Jos where the Jucumari lives, the Jucumari, it often eats people, it is called San Jos.
tyonompo te to pjokni tkjare San Jos towo eto to Ukumari , eto Ukumari eto tanikojno no chane eto , eto tkijare San Jos
Se fueron all, que se llama San Jos, donde habita el jucumari, ese se lo come a la gente, ese (pueblo) se llama San Jos
There the people went, our ancestors have been whipped, because they did not want the Spanish-speaking people to enter.
enepo nakije eno chaono , eto to tkestarakompo no viyanoviono , jicho wo nawrorii to tsiopano no tkomeriono .
all se fu la gente, fu la poca en que fueron guasqueados nuestros antepasados, porque no queran que entren los carayanas.
this is why then Santos Noco, Jos Santos Noco, he was a student, the man was Trinitario, but it is said that he had been studying in Santa Cruz.
takeei juiti ema Santos Noko , Jose Santos Noko , ema estudiante ema chane trinranu pero eneji makarawoiirii te to Santa Cruz .
Por eso ahora santos Noco, Jos Santos Noco, era estudiante, el hombre era trinitario, pero se dice que estudi en Santa Cruz,
There the man had studied earlier,
el hombre all estudi en ese entonces,
He was small still when he went, people were pitying the man, the man was not good-looking, but his head was good.
chichoricho tyompopka najapanuui ema chane , wo toonanaji ema chane , pero to machuti tyuuna
era pequeo todava cuando se fu, le tuvieron lstima al hombre, no era bonito el hombre, pero tena buena cabeza,
So that the man was a student, when he came in here, he really knew how to speak Spanish.
asike ema chane esturiareko , te tsioppo oni jee muetkogiereko tkomeri .
as es que el hombre era estudiante, cuando ingres aqu, saba hablar el castellano.
And he had a magic book, Jos Santos Noco had this.
Ene etjooi to mayee libro mgico , eto makoye ema Jose Santos Noko ,
Y tena su libro magico, eso tena Jos Santos Noco,
So he was learned, the man was speaking like the lawyers, the doctors.
takeei mkatarii , abogadono , roktorono [ no ] makutechjisraai ema chane ,
por eso era inteligente (nadie le ganaba), el hombre hablaba igual que los abogados, doctores,
So that they wanted to know him, who could be this Trinitario Jos Santos Noco, he knew well how to write.
takeei ema nawooo naemotyore ema , majpuka ema trinranrii Jos Santos Nokorii , ema muetkoris to tkajre .
por eso queran conocerlo, quien era ese trinitario Jos Santos Noco, l saba escribir bin.
When the people were getting lost, um, they did not want to be killed, another authority came in and the poor people were hiding there.
Te to temtikporipo no chaono , manjee , wipo ( nau ) nawroo to nakoparaka ; tsioppo ma pona tparaako , ene enochichano terajriikowonrii ene onogi .
Cuando fueron perdiendose la gente, este, ya no queran que los maten, entr otra autoridad y los pobrecitos estaban escondidos all.
And :"Don't worry", said Jos Santos Noco.
Ene : " wo akuuyoko " majichpuiji ema Jos Santos Noko ,
Y "No tengan pena," dice que los dijo Jos Santos Noco,
"Don't worry, gentlemen, I'm going to look into it, I am going to write to the authority in Trinidad", he said, "so I'm going to look into it".
" wo akuuyoko tatanoviono nimarine , nkajreyre jmakni tparaako te to Trinra " makepo , " asike nimarine nuti ".
"No tengan pena seores, y lo voy a ver, voy a escribrir a la autoridad de Trinidad" dijo, "as es que yo lo voy a ver".
And since he had special powers, he got everything (lit. there was his catching), Jos Santos Noco,
Ene komo ema titpaajiorii ema etjooi to makootoorii ema Jos Santos Noko ,
Y como el era inteligente tena su poder Jos Santos Noca saba, (litt. habia lo que l agarra)
He knew, really, the man was a student twenty years in the school in Santa Cruz, so that the man was learned.
muetko jechu estudiante veinte au te eskuela te to Santa Cruz ema chane , takeei mkatarii ema chane .
era bin estudiante veinte aos en la escuela de Santa Cruz el hombre, por eso era inteligente el hombre.
"Now it is necessary that we put our children to school, they are equal to the Spanish-speaking ones in their knowledge" so said the poor man, yes.
" Juiti eto takomnuui eto to wnoka te to eskaera eno vchichanoviono , nakutirichu eno tkomeriono to naetkogne ", ene makeei ma chanetcha ema jee
"Hoy es necesario que pongamos en la escuela a nuestros hijos, ya que son iguales a los carayanas (gente blanca) en sus conocimientos", as dijo el pobre hombre,
They put him (in a high position) because he was knowledgeable, they made Jos Santos Noco a corregidor.
nakosioppo te to [ techem ] muechemrairarii ema , nakosioppo koregieroopo ema Jose Santos Noko .
NB Claudio: es su forma de entender de l

analyse de muechemra'irari'i ? de pense que echemra'i, comme imora'i s'est verbalis, et donc on peut le nominaliser avec -ira; ou alors -ra = POSS pour insister sur le fait que c'est bien sa faon a lui de faire
a l por ejemplo lo metieron porque era entendido, a l lo metieron de corregidor a Jos Santos Noco.
He fixed, he made the village, he named the corregidor, the capitan grande, the caciques, he delegates responsibilities to many of them.
muetpiriko , manokpo eto to wsare , manokpo eno tparaakono , ( ma... ) manokpo ma koregieroru , kapitn grande, no kasikiono , no nasimtuwono eno manoko matuparako
Lo arregl, hizo el pueblo, posesion a las autoridades [ ] posesion al corregidor, capitn grande, a los casiques, a otros deleg atribuciones
And the man had a high position. He, um... he knew well, the man was knowledgeable.
ene ema chane chopetuparao emajicho , manjee , muetkognejcha , techemrai ema chane
je suppose que c'est emajichu, vrifier
y el hombre con gran autoridad. ese s, este, sabe bin, es bin entendido el hombre
And he was not tyrannic, he was not bad, he was going straight when he spoke, he taught the people.
ene wo tkojchochigia , wo winarajina , matupiru to muechjisra , muemitko eno chaono .
y no es dspota, no es malo, tiene una vida recta (ejemplar), les guia a la gente,
Yes, I have been saying so, Lady, Lady Frances.
